Messages.Content:
Thanks for reaching out to us for support. We would love to help you. When you have a free moment, please DM us the version of 
iTunes your running on your computer so that we can look into this together. Also, do you have a backup of your music as well?

Thanks for the information. Other than your phone, are you seeing the correct album art in iTunes? Do you use either Apple Music 
or iTunes Match service? Are you missing any music now that your phone sync’d with your computer?

To confirm, do you sync your iPhone with iTunes on your computer in order to get your music onto your phone? Or do you also have 
Apple Music or iTunes Match?
Okay. Have you tried re-syncing any of the music with incorrect album artwork? If not, let’s try that next.
Got it. Try resyncing it and let us know how it goes.

To clarify, other than connecting the iPhone did you try syncing using the steps outlined here: https://s.apple.com/dE0n2U4M9Y 

If not, try resyncing and let us know the results. We understand your reservations but can assure you this is an important step to help work towards 
a resolution.

@Apple I hooked my #iPhone13 up to my iTunes on my computer, and all my album covers are now wrong. This is driving me insane. 
Thanks. @Apple @AppleSupport
